 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how does one perform purification?\u201d The Prophet called for a vessel of water, then he washed his hands three times, then he washed his face three times,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25513,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/wudu-ears-new-water\/","url_meta":{"origin":25519,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping ears with new water in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Zaid reported: He saw the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, performing ablution and using water for his ears that was different from what he used for his head. Source: al-Sunan al-Kubra\u0301 308 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0632\u064a\u062f \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32982,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/salat-masjid-nafilah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25519,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Prayer, walking to mosque an additional virtue","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah al-Sunabihi reported: The Messenger of Allah, pea